@{b}MBDF@{ub}
This one infects the system, finder and any applications. It does not damage, but it may cause 
regular system and program crashes. It spreads under System 6 and 7. These 3 games "Tetracycle",
"10 Tile Puzzle" and "Obnoxious Tetris" contain this Trojan virus.
Strains: @{b}MBDF A, MBDF B.@{ub}

@{b}MDEF@{ub}
These viruses are not malicious in intent, but can cause system crashes and other unexplained 
behaviour. An infected program may have garbled pull-down menus.
Strains: @{b}MDEF A, MDEF B, MDEF C, MDEF D.@{ub}
Aliases: @{b}Garfield@{ub} (MDEF A), @{b}Top Cat@{ub} (MDEF B).

@{b}MDEF-E & MDEF-F @{ub}
Are simple and benign viruses. They infect applications and system files, and do not cause intentional
file damage.

@{b}Merry XMas@{ub}
The Merry Xmas virus infects HyperCard docs and has several strains. This virus can cause irreparable
damage to Hypercard docs by adding or deleting scripts. Delete infected docs instead of repairing 
them, where ever possible.

@{b}Mosaic Trojan @{ub}
Is a program that is supposed to display graphics, but actually mangles directory structures.
This is a @{b}very destructive virus.@{ub}

@{b}nVIR Family@{ub}
This virus infects the System file and applications. If MacinTalk is installed in your System folder,
your computer will occasionally say "Don't Panic" or it may beep unexpectedly. It can also cause 
programs and the System to crash. @{b}Some strains are destructive.@{ub}
Strains:@{b} AIDS, Fuck, Hpat, J-nVIR, Jude, MEV#, MODM, nCAM, nFlu, nVIR A/B/C, prod, zero.@{ub}

@{b}NVP & NVP Trojan@{ub}
When launched, the NVP virus stops these letters "a,e,i,o,u" from being typed. NVP does not attempt 
to spread to other files.

@{b}Peace@{ub}
The Peace Virus, is introduced by a HyperCard doc called New Apple Products. This virus infects and 
spreads to system files only. It displays a peace message on March 2, 1988. The virus then self-
destructs, no damage is done.

@{b}Scores@{ub}
This virus spreads rapidly to all applications every time the Mac is restarted. There is one tell 
tale sign that Scores is on your Mac, it changes the Note Pad and Scrapbook files, to dog-eared icons.
Scores causes system crashes and other abnormal problems, especially when printing.
Strains: @{b}Eric, San Jose Flu, NASA, VULT.@{ub}

@{b}SevenDust@{ub}
A family of four viruses which spread both through MDEF resources and a System extension created 
by those resources. Three of these viruses cause no other damage. On the sixth day of the month, one 
may erase all non-application files on the current volume.
Strains:@{b} SevenDust A, SevenDust B, SevenDust C, SevenDust D, SevenDust E, SevenDust F.@{ub}
Also known as: @{b}666, MDEF 9806 A, MDEF 9806 B, MDEF 9806 C, MDEF 9806 D.@{ub}

@{b}Steroid Trojan@{ub}
Control Panel - claims to improve QuickDraw speed, but actually destroys the directory structure of
our hard disk. This is a @{b}very destructive virus.@{ub}

@{b}T4@{ub}
Was in a game called GoMoku (v2/2.1), on the internet. It is a @{b}destructive virus@{ub}, it causes 
significant damage to the system file, extensions and applications. Resulting in an unbootable Mac,
and unusable programs.
Strains: @{b}T4 A, T4 B, T4 C.@{ub}

@{b}T4-D @{ub}
It deletes files other than the System file from the System Folder, and documents. @{b}This is a very 
destructive virus.@{ub}

@{b}Tetricycle Trojan@{ub}
This virus hides in a game called Tetricycle. When it is launched, it infects the System, Finder and 
any applications. It causes System file and program damage.

@{b}Virus Info@{ub}
This trojan virus disguises itself as a program which claims to provide virus info, but when 
launched, will destroys the directory of your hard drive. This is a @{b}very destructive virus.@{ub}

@{b}WDEF@{ub}
The WDEF virus spreads in System 6 via the Desktop file. It does not damage data files, but it can 
cause frequent System crashes. System 7 Desktop files are relatively immune to WDEF, only if you 
rebuild the desktop regularly.
Strains: @{b}WDEF A, WDEF B.@{ub}

@{b}ZUC@{ub}
ZUC and it's strains, infects applications and displays the annoying symptom of controlling the 
movement of the cursor on your screen. Once the infection reaches the Finder file, the computer 
becomes virtually unusable.
Strains: @{b}ZUC A, ZUC B, ZUC C.@{ub}
