@{b}Printer Description @{ub}
This folder contains Postcript2 printer description files or PPDs, and includes PPDs for most of 
Apple's own printers.

@{B}QuickTime @{UB}
Provides built-in multimedia support for applications.

@{B}QuickTime PowerPlug @{UB}
Provides native support of QuickTime for PowerPC-based computers when used in combination with 
QuickTime 2.x.

@{B}QuickTime Musical Instruments @{UB}
Supports 30 Roland Standard MIDI sound samples that can be accessed by QuickTime applications with no
additional MIDI equipment.

@{B}Scripting Additions @{UB}
Extends the AppleScript language with special features, such as finding the date or time of day. With
scripting additions installed, AppleScript acts as if these features are part of the language. 
Scripting additions are required only when a script uses them.

@{B}Serial (Built-In) @{UB}
Used by Open Transport to allow access to the built-in serial port on your computer.

@{B}Shared Library Manager @{UB}
Provides native support for Open Transport.

@{B}Shortcuts @{UB}
Explains common keyboard equivalents and other shortcuts to use in the Finder. You can access Shortcuts
in the Guide (question mark) menu when the Finder is active.

@{B}SimpleText Guide @{UB}
Provides step-by-step instructions for using SimpleText. You can access the SimpleText Guide from the
Guide (question mark) menu, after you open SimpleText.

@{B}SOMobjects for Mac OS @{UB}
Used by OpenDoc. 

@{B}Speech Manager @{UB}
Provides text-to-speech capabilities.  

@{B}SR Monitor @{UB}
Used to monitor and interpret speech.

@{B}Startup Tuner @{UB}
Ensures correctly starting up from the disk selected in the Startup Disk control panel.

@{b}System 7 Tuner @{ub}
For System 7.0, and comes on the System Tune-Up disk. It provided better memory management for the 
initial release of System 7.

@{B}SystemAV @{UB}
Used for audio-video input. Required by the Monitors & Sound control panel.

@{B}System Speech Rules @{UB}
Supports voices and speech dialects.

@{b}Thread Manager @{ub}
Thread Manager is an addition to the Macintosh Toolbox that enables concurrent programming for 
real multi-tasking within an application. Supports cooperative and pre-emptive threads of execution at
the application level, but not at the system level. It has been incorporated into System 7.5 onwards.

@{B}TokenTalk Phase 2 @{UB}
