@{B}TokenTalk Prep @{UB}
Provides driver support for TokenTalk Phase II.

@{B}Tutorial Items @{UB}
Provides instructions for learning basic skills on your computer. You can access the tutorial from the
Guide (question mark) menu when the Finder is active. 

@{b}Video Out Default (PAL) @{ub}
Used by the Apple Video Player. On the standard U.S. System, the default video-out for the Apple 
Video Player is NTSC. Outside of the US, the standard video format is PAL - this extension changes 
the Apple Video Player default to PAL.

@{B}Video Startup @{UB}
Used by the Apple Video Player.

@{B}Voices folder @{UB}
Contains voices for use by Speech/ PlainTalk/ Text-to-Speech.

@{B}WorldScript Power Adapter @{UB}
Supports language kit software on PowerPC-based computers. However, computers that use the Roman 
alphabet (English and French, for example), can still take advantage of performance and stability 
enhancements provided by the WorldScript Power Adapter.
