@NODE oddEXTs "Contents / Useful MacOS Information / Extensions / Odd Extensions"

@{JCENTER}@{b}OTHER EXTENSIONS@{ub}
@{JLEFT}
These will probably not be installed on later System OSs, eg. 7.5 to 8.1, although it depends 
entirely on the MacOS you are running, the processor, and any added hardware, such as; a CD-ROM drive,
Ethernet, SCSI etc. 99% of these will not apply to you, so you can safely bin them.

@{B}A/ROSE @{UB}
Allows communication between your computer's main logic board and NuBus cards that run the Apple 
Real-Time Operating System. Examples of such NuBus cards include the Apple Token Ring 4.16 NB card 
and the Apple Serial NB card.

@{b}ADBReInit @{ub}
ADB is a port on the Mac, which you use to plug in the keyboard and mouse. The ADBReInit extension 
prevents memory from being moved at interrupt time, which could cause the some PowerBook and Quadra 
models to hang or crash.

@{b}EXTRANEOUS APPLEGUIDE ADDITIONS: 
-PB 500 Upgrade Guide Additions 
-PB 190 Upgrade Guide Additions 
-PB 2300 Upgrade Guide Additions 
-PB 5300 Upgrade Guide Additions 
-PowerBook Guide Additions @{ub}
Adds step-by-step instructions for using features specific to Powerbook Macintoshs.

@{B}Apple Built-In Ethernet @{ub}/@{b} Apple Ethernet NB@{UB}
A driver for the built-in Ethernet port on Nubus-based Macs.

@{b}Apple Event Manager @{ub}
Allows applications (including the Finder) to send commands to other applications (again, including 
the Finder). For example, in InformINIT, when you click on the little "IE" AND "NN" buttons, 
InformINIT sends an Apple Event to Netscape telling it to go to the URL listed. This file is 
incorporated into the AppleScript extension with System 7.5 and above.

@{B}AppleTalk ImageWriter @{UB}
Enables your computer to print documents on a networked ImageWriter II.

@{b}AppleVision @{ub}
Only used for support of AppleVision monitors only.

@{b}AudioVision @{ub}
Part of the AudioVision 14" monitor software package. Only needed on pre-7.5 systems.

@{b}Assistant Toolbox @{ub}
This is the base extension for AutoRemounter. AutoRemounter works on Macintosh PowerBook computers 
and allows file synchronisation, battery management, and easy mobile computing. It also provides 
support for a persistent RAM disk and deferred printing. This extension may conflict with the 
LaserWriter Select 310 printer software to block printing. A solution is to turn off background 
printing in the Chooser.

@{b}At Ease 7.5 Layer Patch @{ub}
Fixes a crash when using At Ease, and the Show Desktop box is unchecked in the General Controls 
control panel.

@{b}At Ease Startup @{ub}
Forces your Mac to start up with the At Ease instead of the standard Mac Finder.

@{B}AV Setup @{UB}
Used to control AppleVision displays.

@{b}Caps Lock @{ub}
Provides a visual indication of the state of the Caps Lock key on a Macintosh PowerBook. When Caps
Lock is turned on, an Up arrow appears in the menu bar next to the Guide (?) menu. (Not needed on
Macintosh PowerBook 500 series computers.) 

@{b}CFM Update @{ub}
Installed by older versions of QuickDraw 3D. CFM stands for Code Fragment Manager.

@{b}DAL @{ub}
Enables network activity using Data Access Language, formerly called CL/1.
Data Access Language is Apple's client/server protocol for remote data access and is based on ANSI 
standard SQL (Structured Query Language). DAL is optimised to provide decision-support applications 
with uniform access to data, regardless of the different brands of databases, the different host 
platforms, or the different types of networks.

@{b}Desktop Printer Menu @{ub}
Creates a menu bar which allows you to change to a different printer without having to use the
Chooser.

@{b}Display Enable @{ub}
Provides multiscan/multisync support, especially for AppleVision monitors. Adds functionality to 
Energy Saver, and to the Monitors control strip module by allowing you to switch resolutions 
on-the-fly.

@{b}DoubleTrouble @{ub}
For use under pre-System 7.5 systems. When using a debugging utility, the DoubleTrouble extension will
break into the debugger to alert you whenever the code in a project attempts to free a "handle" that
has already been freed. An unsupported Apple extension. NOTE: do not use this extension with 
System 7.5 or later. It is intended only for pre-7.5 use.

@{b}Ethernet (Built-In) @{ub}
Used by Open Transport to allow access to the built-in Ethernet port on on PCI Macs. Not to be 
confused with the Apple Built-In Ethernet extension.

@{b}EthertalkPrep @{ub}
On older systems, worked with Ethertalk Phase 2 to establish and maintain Ethernet connections.
No longer needed under 7.5.3.

@{b}FontSize Patch @{ub}
Fixes problems with font corruption when using the Asian language kits under System 7.5.3 and later.

@{b}Frontmost Extension @{ub}
Frontmost comes with the full AppleScript commercial product, it allows you to create sophisticated 
user interfaces for AppleScript applications. It also acts as a run-time assistant for projects saved
as miniature applications.

@{b}GetInfo @{ub}
For use only under System 7.0. Provides extra information about files which depend on other files by
modifying the Get Info... box. Only works with applications that use QuickTime.

@{b}Graphics Accelerator @{ub}
Provides video acceleration for PCI Macs using an ATI video card.

@{b}Hardware System Update 1.0/2.0/3.0 @{ub}
System 7.1 Updates. Provided numerous system-level improvements. This file was not designed for use 
on Performa models.
 Version 2.0 adds further improvements and overall stability, while version 3.0 increases reliability
and performance, even further. AV Systems already have these improvements in their ROMs.

@{b}IIci/IIsi Monitors @{ub}
Describes the capabilities of the built-in video card for the Macintosh IIci and IIsi. If you remove 
this file, your computer can still use the video card and you can still select the number of colours 
displayed on your monitor, but monitor options (such as gamma settings) may not be available.

@{b}InLine Filter @{ub}
Helps AppleScript and PlainTalk Speech Recognition work together. Allows Worldscript users to type
scripts "in-line" instead of to a separate text file.

@{b}Insomnia @{ub}
Created for Apple PowerBooks to keep them from falling asleep.

@{b}LC Monitors Extension @{ub}
Adds functionality to the Monitors control panel for LC series Macs.

@{b}Letterhead @{ub}
Is part of the QuickDraw GX package, this extension enables the Letterhead paper type option in the
Page Setup window of all GX compatible applications.

@{b}LocalTalk DMA @{ub}
Is part of the obscure System 7.5.3 Revision 2.1, this file fixes a bug with transferring files over
LocalTalk on Performa 6400/180 and 6400/200 computers. This fix is included in the System 7.5.5 
Update.

@{b}MIDI Manager @{ub}
Enables Apple's MIDI Management system.

@{b}Modem Scripts @{ub}
A folder which contains the modem descriptions/scripts used by OT/PPP and Apple Remote Access to 
communicate with your modem.

@{b}Mount IDE Drive @{ub}
Allows Macs with IDE hard drives to mount these drives when the Mac is booted from another disk or 
device.

@{b}N-Up Printing @{ub}
Part of the QuickDraw GX package, this extension allows you to print more than one page on a single 
sheet of paper by dividing the page into smaller sections and reducing the printing size. Up to 16 
pages can be printed on a single 8.5x11 sheet.

@{b}Network Launch Fix @{ub}
On 68040 Macs, fixed a bug when launching applications over a network. Incorporated into system 7.5 
and later.

@{b}PC Net Exchange @{ub}
Works with the PC Exchange control panel to help Mac users share DOS/Windows files over an AppleTalk 
network with users of the AppleShare Client for Windows software.

@{b}Printer Selector @{ub}
Under LaserWriter 8.4 and above, this adds a menu of configured printers to your menu bar for quick 
printer switching.

@{b}ProDOS File System @{ub}
Allowed pre-7.5 Macs to recognize ProDOS/Apple IIe disks. Incorporated into PC Exchange 2.0.2 and 
later, and is incompatible with System 7.5.x.

@{b}PowerBook Monitors Extension @{ub}
Describes the PowerBook built-in display. If you remove this file, your computer can still use the 
PowerBook video card and you can still select the number of colours your screen can display, but 
certain options (such as gamma settings) may not be available.

@{b}PowerPC Monitors Extension @{ub}
Supports Apple's AudioVision 14 monitor.

@{b}Quadra AV Monitors Extension @{ub}
Describes the capabilities of the built-in video card for the Macintosh Quadra and Centris AV 
computers. If you remove this file, your computer can still use the video card and you can still 
select the number of colours displayed on your monitor, but monitor options (such as gamma settings) 
may not be available.

@{b}Quadra Monitors Extension @{ub}
Describes the capabilities of the built-in video card for the Macintosh Quadra and Macintosh Centris 
computers. If you remove this file, your computer can still use the video card and you can still 
select the number of colours displayed on your monitor, but monitor options (such as gamma settings) 
may not be available.

@{b}Scanner @{ub}
Is a driver for all Apple scanners (including 3rd party compatible scanners).

@{b}SCSI Manager @{ub}
Version 4.3 is incorporated into the System under System 7.5.3 and later. On earlier systems, this is 
a SCSI driver upgrade extension for all (real) Macintoshs, with in-built SCSI.

@{b}SCSI Update @{ub}
Included with the AppleShare IP 5.0 beta. Updates the SCSI Manager to allow asynchronous access on 
machines that don't already support it, such as 680x0 machines and early PowerMacs. The new SCSI 
Manager is required for products such as the Advanced Driver Toolkit from Dantz for accessing Digital
Linear Tapes from within Retrospect.

@{b}SerialDMA v2.02 @{ub}
Is a driver update for DMA chips for PPC and 68040 Macs.
Serial DMA is now incorporated into the System file from System 7.5.3 onwards. 

@{b}Sound Manager @{ub}
Sound Manager 3.2 was incorporated into the System in System 7.5.3, and included asynchronous sound 
playback. Version 3.2.1 is part of the QuickTime 2.5 package and provides even better low-memory 
performance and better multi-channel sound via a new sound clock component. Sound Manager 3.2.1 is 
built into the System file under 7.6.

@{b}Startup Tuner @{ub}
Part of the System 7.5.3 revision, fixes a problem with the Startup Disk control panel where the Mac 
(on selected models) may not startup from the selected disk. Not necessary for System 7.5.5 and later.

@{b}Stationary @{ub}
Part of the QuickDraw GX package, this extension enables the Stationary paper type option in the 
Page Setup.. window of compatible applications.

@{b}TokenTalk Phase 2 @{ub}
Driver used by the Apple Token Ring card and the Network/AppleTalk control panels.

@{b}Video Startup @{ub}
Provides support for the Apple Video Player; needed to use the AVP.

@{b}WindowPicker @{ub}
Older, unsupported utility which provides the ability to bring any open window to the front via a 
pop-up menu and/or arrow keys.

@{b}Shutdown Items enabler @{ub}
Provides support for the Shutdown Items folder under System 7 Pro.
