@NODE Libs "Contents / Useful MacOS Information / Libraries"

@{JCENTER}@{b}LIBRARIES@{ub}
@{JLEFT}
Shared libraries are modules of data/code that is used by many applications. They are loaded only when
needed, and not during boot-up. They must be placed either, in the Extensions folder (if copied there
by the installer) or in the same folder as the program. Libraries often appear in Systems 7.5 to 8.1.

@{JCENTER}@{b}Select one of these buttons to go to the other categories: @{ub}
@{" Control Panels " LINK CPs} @{" Extensions " LINK Extensions} @{" System Folder " LINK SystemFolder} @{" System Enablers " LINK SysEnable} @{" Menu " LINK Info}
@{JLEFT}

@{B}AppleScriptLib @{UB}
Provides native support for AppleScript on PowerPC-based computers. 

@{b}ColorSyncLib 68k @{ub}
Code Fragment Manager file for the ColourSync software.

@{b}DisplayLib @{ub}
Provides backwards compatibility for Display Manager 2.0 functionality on pre-7.5 systems. The 
Display Manager allows users and applications to dynamically change the arrangement and display modes
of monitors attached to the computer.

@{b}DragLib @{ub}
It is a drag and drop support library which is incorporated into the Macintosh Drag and Drop 
extension. Included in the System software under System 7.5+.

@{b}Game Sprockets:
  DrawSprocketLib, GoggleSprocketLib, InputSprocketLib, NetSprocketLib, SoundSprocketLib @{ub}
The game sprocket system was developed as a way for game developers to directly access certain 
features of the System software, such as networking, video and audio, and also to provide added 
game-oriented functionality to these areas. The individual sprocket modules provide shared library 
support for their respective features.

@{b}ColorSyncLib68K, NuDragLib.slb, NuQuickTimeLib.slb, NuThreadsLib.slb, NuTranslationLib.slb
QuickDraw GX Enabler @{ub}
These files are 68K shared libraries which work with the CFM-68K Runtime Enabler extension. They are
loaded by the CFM-68K Runtime Enabler extension if a CFM68K based application needs them.

@{b}ObjectSupportLib @{ub}
Provides services to allow applications to send, receive and exchange Apple Events that conform to 
the object model as well as implementing the Open Scripting Architecture object model.

@{B}OpenDoc Libraries folder @{UB}
Contains code libraries and other files that enable OpenDoc technology. 

@{B}Open Tpt AppleTalk Library @{UB}
Used by Open Transport for the AppleTalk communication protocol.

@{B}Open Tpt Internet Library @{UB}
Used by Open Transport for the TCP/IP communication protocol.

@{B}Open Transport Library @{UB}
Used by Open Transport.

@{B}OpenTptAppleTalkLib @{UB}
Used by Open Transport for AppleTalk communication protocol.

@{B}OpenTptInternetLib @{UB}
Used by Open Transport for the TCP/IP communication protocol.

@{B}OpenTransportLib @{UB}
Used by Open Transport.

@{b}PrintingLib @{ub}
Provides shared library support for the LaserWriter 8.4.x software. Needed for 68k Macs and PowerMacs.
