@NODE SystemFolder "Contents / Useful MacOS Information / System Folder"

@{JCENTER}@{B}A STANDARD SYSTEM FOLDER @{UB}

@{JLEFT}
Depending on the type of computer you have, the contents of the System Folder may vary. You might 
also have items or folders that were added by third-party applications.
MacOS 7.5 System Folder @{" Pic " LINK "MacGuideIV_Pics/MT3_SystemFolder/main"}. MacOS 8.1 System Folder @{" Pic " LINK "MacGuideIV_Pics/MT4_MacOS8SysFldr/main"}.
@{JCENTER}
@{b}Select one of these buttons to go to the other categories: @{ub}
@{" Control Panels " LINK CPs} @{" Extensions " LINK Extensions} @{" Libraries " LINK Libs} @{" System Enablers " LINK SysEnable} @{" Menu " LINK Info}
@{JLEFT}

@{b}Finder @{ub}
Displays the desktop area, where you work with files and disks, and keeps track of your files. 

@{b}Apple Menu Items folder@{UB}
When you place an item (folder, application, or document) in this folder, it appears in the Apple 
menu. To create submenus, place folders inside the Apple Menu Items folder.

@{b}Clipboard @{UB}
Temporarily stores the last item you cut or copied from a document.

@{b}Control Panels folder @{UB}
Contains individual control panels. You use control panels to adjust your computer's settings. See 
the "About the Control Panels" document in the Apple Extras folder for more information.

@{b}Control Strip Modules folder @{UB}
Contains modules used by the Control Strip control panel. 

@{b}Editors @{UB}
Contains OpenDoc part editors. Editors provide functionality to OpenDoc parts, but you don't work 
with editors directly. To use an editor to create a document, double-click the editor's stationery 
icon. Your stationery icons are probably located in the Stationery folder on your hard disk. 

@{b}Extensions folder @{UB}
Contains individual extensions that modify the operation of your computer. Unlike a control panel, an
extension works automatically, without your intervention.

@{b}Fonts folder @{UB}
Contains font suitcases or individual font files. You can place up to 128 suitcase or font files in 
this folder. PostScript fonts are not included in the 128 file limit. Font suitcases can hold any 
number of font files, up to a limit of 16 MB. @{" About Fonts Pic " LINK "MacGuideIV_Pics/MT3_Fonts/main"} @{" Types of Fonts Pic " LINK "MacGuideIV_Pics/MT3_FontTypes/main"}

@{b}Launcher Items folder @{UB}
Contains files, folders, and applications that appear in the Launcher window. 

@{b}Macsbug @{UB}
A debugger used by programmers to help diagnose problems with programs, extensions, and so on. Unless
you're programming, you don't need Macsbug.

@{b}Preferences folder @{UB}
Contains preferences files created by individual applications. A preference file determines 
application settings.

@{b}PrintMonitor Documents folder @{UB}
Stores all spooled print documents waiting to be printed. 

@{b}Scrapbook @{UB}
Stores items placed in the Scrapbook (the Scrapbook is available in the Apple menu). 

@{b}Shutdown Items folder @{UB}
Contains applications or scripts that run automatically when you shut down your computer. You can add
or remove items from this folder.

@{b}Startup Items folder @{UB}
Contains applications or scripts that run automatically when you start your computer. You can add or
remove items from this folder.

@{b}System Enabler xxx@{ub}
Is an System updater file, that makes a @{b}specific @{ub}Macintosh work with older System software,
ie. System 7.1x with a Power Mac 7500. See @{" Enablers in detail " LINK SysEnable} for details.

@{b}System file @{ub}
Contains some system-wide resources, such as sounds and keyboard layouts.
@ENDNODE

